wiki.content: Rich The Kid posted a snippet of “Plug Walk” on Twitter on January 17, 2018, eventually premiering the track on January 20, 2018. The song was released a day earlier than its expected release date of February 8, 2018 via Zane Lowe’s Beats 1 show. The phrase “plug walk” was popularized by Black Kray (now known as SICKBOYRARI) in 2014 with his single of the same name. The track’s cover features an astronaut floating in space, performing a space walk. “Space walking” is the process in which astronauts on the International Space Station exit the station and perform mechanical work on the exterior of the vehicle. Rich incorporates this within the title of the track and the repeated theme throughout the song. Additionally, the instrumentals of the track include a variety of lead pads and spacey synths, creating an out-of-this-world vibe. The space theme is continued throughout the track, with many mentions of “space coupes” and “spaceships.” On March 4th, 2018, almost exactly 1 month after the track’s release date, Rich released the music video. Directed by Daps, the video was inspired by a scene from the pilot episode of the 2008 TV series Breaking Bad in which the main character, Walter White, creates a poisonous gas inside his RV meth lab in an attempt to kill two drug dealers and eliminate his competition. Rich explained the Breaking Bad theme in an interview with TMZ: "I really like the—the show. I like Walter, and I’m the trap Walter, you know what I’m sayin'? I’m Breaking Bad in the kitchen." In the video, Rich can be seen hanging out with the Instagram-famous rubber alien Lil Mayo, some almost-naked women, and a lot of various drugs. Though it’s clear that the scene is borrowed from the Breaking Bad episode, the video’s setting might be the infamous Area 51, considering the fact that it’s in a desert and there’s an incorporation of aliens and spaceships.
